<p>Rather than walking the whole way home or taking the train or a cab, Bella and one of her friends splurged on a Revel scooter, a rentable electric scooter.</p>

<p>The company has mopeds strewn throughout New York City, Miami, Austin, San Francisco, Oakland and Washington, D.C.</p>

<p>Customers can reserve a nearby scooter through an app, then pay $1 to unlock and 35 cents for each minute they're riding.</p>

<p>Service was temporarily suspended in New York City over the summer after two people were killed in scooter crashes.</p>

